    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## AI Password Guessing Assistant\r\n\r\nSimulate how an AI trained on leaked password data might try to guess a new user’s password.\r\n\r\n### Do This:\r\nYou’ve already tried guessing passwords for a fictional user based on their interests and personal info. Now see what the AI comes up with.\r\n\r\n1. Load Maya's profile from the library.\r\n2. Ask the AI to generate a list of example passwords for Maya that reflect **common real-world patterns**.\r\n3. What patterns do you notice in its guesses?\r\n4. How similar are they to the ones you created?\r\n\r\nCompare the AI’s responses to your own predictions. \r\n\r\n---\r\n**Try it out!** \r\n\r\n:::details [<i class=\"fa fa-briefcase\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Need a starting prompt?**]\r\n>Here is Maya's profile. Generate a list of example passwords for Maya that reflect common real-world patterns.\r\n:::\r\n&nbsp\r\n\r\n\r\n::: details [<i class=\"fa fa-file-image-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **How do I add a user profile?**]\r\n- Click the button labeled **Add** below your chat input.\r\n- Choose **From Library**\r\n- Then browse the existing files.\r\n- When you find your user's file to upload, click the checkbox next to it to select it and then click **Attach**.\r\n- You should see the file get added to the message being sent to AI Chat.\r\n:::\r\n",
